Christina Pitt Former ANC MP Vytjie Mentor has praised Winnie Madikizela-Mandela at a memorial service in Cape Town. (Paul Herman, News24) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Former ANC MP Vytjie Mentor praised Winnie Madikizela-Mandela for her "golden heart" at a memorial service for the struggle hero at St George's Cathedral in Cape Town on Thursday. Madikizela-Mandela died on Monday at the age of 81. Mentor reminisced about how Madikizela-Mandela cared for her when she was a political prisoner in Johannesburg "Sun City" Medium B prison. ALSO READ: 'Winnie didn't kill Stompie Seipei' – Vytjie Mentor "When my own family disowned me because I was a political prisoner, I was kept by Mama Winnie Mandela with her golden heart," said Mentor. She also mentioned that Madikizela-Mandela bought her her first bottle of perfume and silk pyjamas. "She did not know me. She had never met me. She just heard there was a teacher incarcerated at Sun City and it was my birthday," said Mentor. ALSO READ: 'Some of us are very hurt by' negative comments about Mam' Winnie - Yengeni "When she heard that no one was visiting me for a long time, she organised a family from East Berlin to adopt me – to write letters to me, to send socks to me in winter. That is the heart of a revolutionary." Mentor believes that her generation had a special bond with Madikizela-Mandela. "I come from the generation of young lions – the generation that was carried by Winnie Mandela," she said.  RELATED - WATCH: Trevor Manuel calls on Magashule to account for Winnie's Brandfort house money   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  